summary: The call was from a customer who was having trouble with their password and wanted to know how it would appear while entering it. Agent Deeksha guided the customer to click on 'Forgot Password' to create a new password. The customer mentioned that the option to enter a new password was not visible on their mobile. Deeksha suggested trying on another phone. The customer wanted to do it on a different mobile but was unsure of the password. Deeksha patiently instructed the customer to create a new password and check what was displayed on the screen. The customer seemed confused about the process and requested Deeksha to provide the password, which Deeksha explained was personal and needed to be created by the customer. The customer then asked for the new password, indicating that the system was asking for the old password first. Deeksha advised the customer to change the password by clicking on 'Forgot Password' and explained the login options available. The customer seemed to struggle with following the instructions on their phone. Deeksha patiently guided the customer on how to install the application on the new phone and login. The call ended with the customer agreeing to try the steps provided by Deeksha. Overall, Deeksha remained patient and tried to assist the customer in resolving the issue with their password.

summary:
The call was from a customer named Avishay Varma to the company agent Abhishek at Choice Phoenix. Avishay Varma was calling to inquire about checking his share in Solanbiri. The conversation was a bit disjointed with the agent asking for the customer's name and the name of the share. The agent mentioned having shares in Essentia. The customer seemed to be asking about the procedure for buying shares and mentioned receiving a link via email for making payments. The agent confirmed that the link for payment would be sent via email and needed to be clicked to make the payment, failing which the share would be automatically lost. The customer insisted on checking the email for the link and urged the agent to make the payment. The call ended with the customer asking the agent to call back after making the payment.

Overall, the call seemed to have a few communication gaps and the agent could have been more proactive in guiding the customer through the process of making the payment for the share. The customer appeared a bit impatient and insistent on the agent checking the email for the payment link. The agent, on the other hand, could have been more reassuring and provided clearer instructions to the customer.
